<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,603,629]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body yellowish to yellowish brown (including legs) (
<figureCitation box="[923,1063,603,629]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 10A–C</figureCitation>
), antenna with scape, pedicel and F1–3 clear yellow (
<figureCitation box="[366,467,639,665]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
), then darkened in the following segments; metasoma waxy white in middle of T1 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
) and ventrally. Fore wing hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[594,694,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
), with veins pale brown, except veins r, 1–SR, 1–M, apical half of M + CU, 1–CU1 and 2–CU1 are dark brown; pterostigma mostly pale brown, and dark brown apically. Head and mesosoma finely and closely granulate; mesopleuron and metapleuron are smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1303,747,773]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
); sternaulus deep and linear ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[444,547,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
); propodeum nearly smooth, without distinct fields, with a short median carina, extending from base (
<figureCitation box="[398,504,819,845]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
); vein r of fore wing about as long as or slightly longer than vein 3–SR; vein SR1 straight, but slightly concave apically, reaching wing apex; vein r–m present but not tubular (
<figureCitation box="[1199,1301,855,881]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheath dark brown, about 0.3× as long as metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[745,848,891,917]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" box="[199,1349,927,954]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,927,953]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[352,456,927,953]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[463,484,928,954]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, length of body (excluding ovipositor): 
<quantity box="[933,1018,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1mm</quantity>
.; length of fore wing: 
<quantity box="[1263,1345,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[199,283,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Colour.</emphasis>
Body yellowish to yellowish brown (including legs), antenna with scape, pedicel, and F1–3 clear yellow, rest of flagellum (unbroken part) darkened; mandible yellowish, with black tip; palpi whitish; metasoma waxy white ventrally. Fore wing hyaline, with veins pale brown, except veins r, 1–SR, 1-M, apical half of M + CU, 1–CU1 and 2–CU1 are dark brown; pterostigma mostly pale brown, and dark brown apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,411,1107,1134]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 11A, B</figureCitation>
). Finely granulate dorsally; frons medially, just behind antennal bases, slightly swollen and shiny; area between stemmaticum and antennal bases distinctly depressed; inner orbits of eyes slightly emarginate above; eye in dorsal view 2.6× as long as temple; OOL: OD: POL = 35: 29: 17; malar space 1.3× as long as basal width of mandible; scape equal both ventrally and dorsally; pedicel slightly more swollen than F1, slightly shorter than scape; F1 about 5.0× as long as wide, 1.3× as long as F2; F2–4 about equal sized, 3.8× as long as wide; mandible with two subequal, sharp teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[199,319,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[335,475,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 10A–C</figureCitation>
) 2.0× as long as its height. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum finely granulate; mesoscutum clothed with dense, fine whitish setae, becoming few along lateral and posterior margins of mesoscutellum; notauli very weak to indistinct; propodeum nearly smooth, with a short median longitudinal carina at base not reaching posterior margin; mesopleuron smooth and shiny, with a deep linear sternaulus ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[199,313,1468,1493]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fore wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[329,429,1467,1493]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Vein r arising very near to the middle of pterostigma; SR1 straight, slightly concave near to apex, reaching wing apex; 2–SR+M very short, hardly seen; vein r 0.75× as long as pterostigma width, about slightly longer than vein 3–SR; pterostigma about as long as or slightly longer than vein 1–R1; vein 1–M nearly straight; vein cu–a postfurcal; r: 3–SR: SR1 = 15: 13: 90.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[199,252,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Legs</emphasis>
moderately long and slender; metatibia distinctly longer than hind femur, 1.3×; hind basitarsus slightly shorter than following tarsomeres combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[199,316,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[331,474,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 10A–C</figureCitation>
